      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 2 is a mechanically sound example of the analog driving experience. Powered by a 3.4L naturally aspirated flat-six, the drivetrain features a documented dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a rear main seal replacement. Power is delivered through a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle with a short-throw shifter for precise engagement. The chassis has been enhanced with Bilstein B8 dampers and refreshed control arm bushings, maintaining factory-spec geometry while sharpening turn-in response. The cooling system has been overhauled with a low-temperature thermostat and CSF aluminum radiators to manage thermal loads effectively. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the engine exhibits strong compression across all cylinders and a clean borescope report. A true driver\u2019s car with the mechanical vitals prioritized.",
